      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَبُو عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ ع إِنَّ اَللَّهَ لَمْ يُؤْمِنِ اَلْمُؤْمِنَ مِنْ بَلاَيَا اَلدُّنْيَا وَ لَكِنْ آمَنَهُ مِنَ اَلْعَمَى فِي اَلْآخِرَةِ وَ مِنَ اَلشَّقَاءِ يَعْنِي عَمَى اَلْبَصَرِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.badr-shahin": [
          "(The same previous series of relaters)… from Mohammed bin Ahmed from Muawiya bin Ammar that Abu Abdullah (a) said: Allah has not insured the believers against the worldly misfortunes. In fact, He insures them against the blindness in the Hereafterand the unhappiness –i.e. sightlessness."
        ]
      }
